`.lathe/builder.md` written. Here's what it encodes:

**Identity** — the builder receives goals framed around stakeholders (S1–S5) and their emotional signals. It carries that framing through the implementation to verify the fix actually lands for the person it's meant to help.

**Project conventions** — Helm chart HA gates, autarky checks, shellcheck, contract validator, ArgoCD app requirements, image tag format, values variable conventions. These are durable; snapshot carries current-state health.

**Constitutional gates** — G1/G6/G7/G8/G9 with exact commands. Builder must run all before pushing.

**Brand** — aligned with `brand.md`: SCREAMING_SNAKE verdicts, `will refuse` not `may fail`, one-line success, lowercase action-first commit messages.

**CI model** — builder owns implement/commit/push/PR; engine owns merge. CI failures preempt the goal.

**Changelog format** — includes the "Adjacent work noticed" field so the builder can surface things it saw without grabbing scope that belongs to the goal-setter.
